column26: In the Books section of the Library Management Application, there is no Reset button to clear the search fields and reset the search results. This forces users to manually delete their search inputs and refresh the page to view the complete list of books again, which is inconvenient and unintuitive.

The search bar in the Books section does not include any label, placeholder text, or indication of what fields are searchable (e.g., Book Name, Author). This omission makes it unclear to users how to use the search function effectively.

When searching for a nonexistent book in the Books section, the system does not display a friendly “No books found” message. Instead, it either shows a blank page, stale results from previous searches, or an unclear error, causing confusion for the user.
Searching of all available books by a selected age group not working instead asking for all other field values.
Searching of all available books by a selected book format not working instead asking for all other field values.
Searching of all available books by a selected subject not working instead asking for all other field values.
Searching of all available books by a selected author not working instead asking for all other field values.
System does not display an appropriate error message when a non-existent book is searched.
System does not check for invalid user name. Whatever is written in the “Your Name” field, it shows no error message and form got submitted and shows “Message sent successfully”
System does not show any error message for invalid email id rather form is submitted for invalid mail id also
The system does not check if phone number is valid or not in chat section. Invalid phone number and even any text are got submitted and system shows message “*message sent successfully*”
Members getting added with same card numbers in different membership types.
Form is not reset after submission causing duplicate values adding in the members page
